# Agent Memory Workflow

- At the start of substantial work, read `AGENT-MEMORY.md` after reading any core project memory files.
- Use `AGENT-MEMORY.md` as the current working memory for active priorities and recent decisions.
- After major audits, scope changes, blocker discoveries, or user decisions, update `AGENT-MEMORY.md`.
- Record verified facts, open risks, and current priorities clearly and concisely.
- Do not let `AGENT-MEMORY.md` replace `CLAUDE.md`; it is the current working layer, not the full project history.
- When a conflict appears, flag it and update memory after resolving it.
